rComments: He is the best language prof i've ever had and this is coming from someone who usually struggles with foreign languages. He's very approachable and are about his students. There a lot of group/partner activities so by the end of the class you feel like a family. By far my ultimate favourite prof!!

Makes coming to class worth it, brings classes together so by end of session everyone feels like friends. Class itself is easy but you have to make sure to do the homework to drill the grammar rules and what not into your head. Fair weekly quizzes midterm and final.
Very funny and sassy, but a very though grader. He's helpful and patient with the students. He also teaches us expressions and slang from Colombia, which is pretty cool. All in all, he's good prof.
